<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="507" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,643,776]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,680,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Remarks.</emphasis>
Specimens of this species were not available for study. It was recorded, without figures, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1369,1436,679,703]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[158,244,716,740]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="507">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
) by Dai, Li &amp; Chen (
<number box="[484,546,716,740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="507" value="2004.0">2004</number>
). The species can be distinguished by the asymmetrical aedeagus with the shaft elongate and anterior margin keellike over the basal third, forming a medial asymmetrical process at the base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
